  </div>
</section>

<!-- ABOUT -->
<section id="about">
  <div class="container">
    <p class="section-label">// 01 — Identity</p>
    <h2 class="section-title">About Me</h2>
    <div class="about-grid">
      <div>
        <div class="about-avatar">AM</div>
        <div class="stat-row">
          <div class="stat-item"><div class="dot"></div><span>Holy Angel University — BS CS</span></div>
          <div class="stat-item"><div class="dot"></div><span>Intern @ Geo Pro Global Solutions</span></div>
          <div class="stat-item"><div class="dot"></div><span>Angeles City, Philippines</span></div>
          <div class="stat-item"><div class="dot"></div><span>Full-Stack · Networks · Creative</span></div>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="about-text">
        <p>
          Hi, I'm <span class="highlight">Aldrin</span>—a Computer Science student at
          <span class="highlight-m">Holy Angel University</span> and a
          <span class="highlight">Full-Stack Developer</span> currently interning at
          <span class="highlight-y">Geo Pro Global Solutions</span>.
        </p>
        <p>
          My approach to tech is a bit like a puzzle. To build great software, I believe you need
          to understand how the pieces connect—from the high-level UI down to the wires.
          That's why I've spent the last few years rounding out my coding with a deep dive
          into <span class="highlight">networking</span>, from CCNA Introduction to Networks
          all the way to Switching, Routing, and Wireless Essentials.
        </p>
        <p>
          I'm a big believer in staying <span class="highlight-m">"student-mode forever."</span>
          I started with PCAP Programming Essentials back in 2022, and I'm capping off
          March 2026 by finalizing my <span class="highlight-y">Python Certification</span>
          from freeCodeCamp.
        </p>
        <p>
          Beyond code, I'm a <span class="highlight">filmmaker</span> (short film competition
          winner with Final Cut Pro), indie game builder, and—someday—the founder of a
          forest-themed café in Angeles City. I build things that are technically sharp
          and deeply human-centered.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

